A YOUNG MAN NAMED RONALD CLARK GREW UP POOR. HE BELIEVED HOWEVER THAT HE WAS RICH. HE TOLD HIS PARENTS THAT THEY WERE RICH, BUT THEY BROKE IT TO HIM THAT THEY WERE NOT. HIS FATHER WORKED AS JANITOR AND THEY LIVED IN A LIBRARY. HE WAS EMBARRARASED ABOUT THERE LIVING CONDITION, BUT HE EVENTUALLY REALIZED THAT WHERE THEY LIVED GAVE HIM THE OPPORTUNITY TO READ AND LEARN SO MUCH. HE WENT ON TO GRADUATION FROM COLLEGE NO ONE FROM PREVIOUS GENERATION GRADUATED FROM HIGHSCHOOL LET ALONE COLLEGE. HE LATER TOOK  HIS FATHER TO HIS JOB WERE HE WAS A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE. OUTSIDE THE ROOM HAD HIS NAME ON A PLAQUE. HIS FATHER DID NOT SAY MUCH BUT HE KNEW THAT HE WAS PROUD OF HI.

A YOUNG MAN THOUGHT HE WAS RICH BUT ACTUALLY GREW UP POOR. THIS WAS REVEILED TO HIM BY HIS PARENTS. THEY LIVED IN A LIBRARY. HE STAYED UP TO 3 AM READING BOOKS. HE EVENTALLY WENT ON TO GRADUATE FROM COLLEGE AS A PROFESSOR. HIS FAMILY MEMBERS HAD ONLY MADE IT AS HIGH AS HIGHSCHOOL WITH OUT GRADUATING. HE SHOWED HIS FATHER HIS OFFICE AS A PROFESSOR THAT HIS NAME ON A PLAGUE. HIS FATHER DID NOT SHOW EMOTION. BUT HE KNEW HE WAS PROUD.
HE WAS EMBARRESSED ABOUT LIVING IN A LIBRARY BUT NEW THIS GAVE HIM A RICH OPPORTUNITY TO LEARN THAT OTHER KIDS DID NOT HAVE. IT PAID OFF IN THE LONG RUN AS HE EVENTUALLY BECAME A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
THIS STORY TOOK PLACE IN THE 1940'S.
HE WAS THE ONLY ONE IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE COLLEGE AND HIGHSCHOOL
